A simple Python Class for a serial-LCD Converter from Sparkfun:

https://www.sparkfun.com/products/258

This class requires the python-serial Module:

$ sudo apt-get install python-dev
$ sudo apt-get install python-serial

The Class contains the following Methods:
	- Init(Device, Baud, Number of Columns per Line)
		Initialize the Class with the given Device and Baudrate for a specified LCD.
	- Clr()
		Clears the LCD.
	- Position(Row, Position)
		Places the Cursor at the specified Position.
	- SetBrightness(Brightness)
		Set the Brightness of the LCD Backlight. Possible Values are 0 (Off) to 30 (max. Power).
	- EnableBlink(Enable)
		Enable (Enable = On) / Disable (Enable = Off) the blinking Cursor.
	- EnableUnderline(Enable)
		Enable (Enable = On) / Disable (Enable = Off) underline the Cursor.
	- EnableVisual(Enable)
		Enable (Enable = On) / Disable (Enable = Off) the LCD Screen.
	- SwitchSplash()
		Toggle the Bootinformation of the PIC Mikroprocessor during Power-Up.
	- SetCursor(CursorPosition)
		Set the Cursor on the specified Position.
	- ChangeBaud(Baud)
		Changes the Baudrate of the Module. Possible Values are 2400, 4800, 9600, 19200 and 38400 
		Baud.
	- Write(Text)
		Write the specified Text to the Display